  15 """Preprocess images and bounding boxes for detection.
  16 
  17 We perform two sets of operations in preprocessing stage:
  18 (a) operations that are applied to both training and testing data,
  19 (b) operations that are applied only to training data for the purpose of
  20     data augmentation.
  21 
  22 A preprocessing function receives a set of inputs,
  23 e.g. an image and bounding boxes,
  24 performs an operation on them, and returns them.
  25 Some examples are: randomly cropping the image, randomly mirroring the image,
  26                    randomly changing the brightness, contrast, hue and
  27                    randomly jittering the bounding boxes.
  28 
  29 The preprocess function receives a tensor_dict which is a dictionary that maps
  30 different field names to their tensors. For example,
  31 tensor_dict[fields.InputDataFields.image] holds the image tensor.
  32 The image is a rank 4 tensor: [1, height, width, channels] with
  33 dtype=tf.float32. The groundtruth_boxes is a rank 2 tensor: [N, 4] where
  34 in each row there is a box with [ymin xmin ymax xmax].
  35 Boxes are in normalized coordinates meaning
  36 their coordinate values range in [0, 1]
  37 
  38 To preprocess multiple images with the same operations in cases where
  39 nondeterministic operations are used, a preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache
  40 object can be passed into the preprocess function or individual operations.
  41 All nondeterministic operations except random_jitter_boxes support caching.
  42 E.g.
  43 Let tensor_dict{1,2,3,4,5} be copies of the same inputs.
  44 Let preprocess_options contain nondeterministic operation(s) excluding
  45 random_jitter_boxes.
  46 
  47 cache1 = preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache()
  48 cache2 = preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache()
  49 a = preprocess(tensor_dict1, preprocess_options, preprocess_vars_cache=cache1)
  50 b = preprocess(tensor_dict2, preprocess_options, preprocess_vars_cache=cache1)
  51 c = preprocess(tensor_dict3, preprocess_options, preprocess_vars_cache=cache2)
  52 d = preprocess(tensor_dict4, preprocess_options, preprocess_vars_cache=cache2)
  53 e = preprocess(tensor_dict5, preprocess_options)
  54 
  55 Then correspondings tensors of object pairs (a,b) and (c,d)
  56 are guaranteed to be equal element-wise, but the equality of any other object
  57 pair cannot be determined.
  58 
  59 Important Note: In tensor_dict, images is a rank 4 tensor, but preprocessing
  60 functions receive a rank 3 tensor for processing the image. Thus, inside the
  61 preprocess function we squeeze the image to become a rank 3 tensor and then
  62 we pass it to the functions. At the end of the preprocess we expand the image
  63 back to rank 4.
  64 """

  91 def _apply_with_random_selector(x,
  92                                 func,
  93                                 num_cases,
  94                                 preprocess_vars_cache=None,
  95                                 key=''):
  96   """Computes func(x, sel), with sel sampled from [0...num_cases-1].
  97 
  98   If both preprocess_vars_cache AND key are the same between two calls, sel will
  99   be the same value in both calls.
 100 
 101   Args:
 102     x: input Tensor.
 103     func: Python function to apply.
 104     num_cases: Python int32, number of cases to sample sel from.
 105     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
 106                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
 107                            function is called multiple times with the same
 108                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
 109     key: variable identifier for preprocess_vars_cache.
 110 
 111   Returns:
 112     The result of func(x, sel), where func receives the value of the
 113     selector as a python integer, but sel is sampled dynamically.
 114   """
 115   generator_func = functools.partial(
 116       tf.random_uniform, [], maxval=num_cases, dtype=tf.int32)
 117   rand_sel = _get_or_create_preprocess_rand_vars(
 118       generator_func, preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache.SELECTOR,
 119       preprocess_vars_cache, key)
 120 
 121   # Pass the real x only to one of the func calls.
 122   return control_flow_ops.merge([func(
 123       control_flow_ops.switch(x, tf.equal(rand_sel, case))[1], case)
 124                                  for case in range(num_cases)])[0]

 127 def _apply_with_random_selector_tuples(x,
 128                                        func,
 129                                        num_cases,
 130                                        preprocess_vars_cache=None,
 131                                        key=''):
 132   """Computes func(x, sel), with sel sampled from [0...num_cases-1].
 133 
 134   If both preprocess_vars_cache AND key are the same between two calls, sel will
 135   be the same value in both calls.
 136 
 137   Args:
 138     x: A tuple of input tensors.
 139     func: Python function to apply.
 140     num_cases: Python int32, number of cases to sample sel from.
 141     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
 142                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
 143                            function is called multiple times with the same
 144                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
 145     key: variable identifier for preprocess_vars_cache.
 146 
 147   Returns:
 148     The result of func(x, sel), where func receives the value of the
 149     selector as a python integer, but sel is sampled dynamically.
 150   """
 151   num_inputs = len(x)
 152   generator_func = functools.partial(
 153       tf.random_uniform, [], maxval=num_cases, dtype=tf.int32)
 154   rand_sel = _get_or_create_preprocess_rand_vars(
 155       generator_func, preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache.SELECTOR_TUPLES,
 156       preprocess_vars_cache, key)
 157 
 158   # Pass the real x only to one of the func calls.
 159   tuples = [list() for t in x]
 160   for case in range(num_cases):
 161     new_x = [control_flow_ops.switch(t, tf.equal(rand_sel, case))[1] for t in x]
 162     output = func(tuple(new_x), case)
 163     for j in range(num_inputs):
 164       tuples[j].append(output[j])
 165 
 166   for i in range(num_inputs):
 167     tuples[i] = control_flow_ops.merge(tuples[i])[0]
 168   return tuple(tuples)
 169 
 170 
 171 def _get_or_create_preprocess_rand_vars(generator_func,
 172                                         function_id,
 173                                         preprocess_vars_cache,
 174                                         key=''):
 175   """Returns a tensor stored in preprocess_vars_cache or using generator_func.
 176 
 177   If the tensor was previously generated and appears in the PreprocessorCache,
 178   the previously generated tensor will be returned. Otherwise, a new tensor
 179   is generated using generator_func and stored in the cache.
 180 
 181   Args:
 182     generator_func: A 0-argument function that generates a tensor.
 183     function_id: identifier for the preprocessing function used.
 184     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
 185                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
 186                            function is called multiple times with the same
 187                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
 188     key: identifier for the variable stored.
 189   Returns:
 190     The generated tensor.
 191   """
 192   if preprocess_vars_cache is not None:
 193     var = preprocess_vars_cache.get(function_id, key)
 194     if var is None:
 195       var = generator_func()
 196       preprocess_vars_cache.update(function_id, key, var)
 197   else:
 198     var = generator_func()
 199   return var

 202 def _random_integer(minval, maxval, seed):
 203   """Returns a random 0-D tensor between minval and maxval.
 204 
 205   Args:
 206     minval: minimum value of the random tensor.
 207     maxval: maximum value of the random tensor.
 208     seed: random seed.
 209 
 210   Returns:
 211     A random 0-D tensor between minval and maxval.
 212   """
 213   return tf.random_uniform(
 214       [], minval=minval, maxval=maxval, dtype=tf.int32, seed=seed)

 217 # TODO(mttang): This method is needed because the current
 218 # tf.image.rgb_to_grayscale method does not support quantization. Replace with
 219 # tf.image.rgb_to_grayscale after quantization support is added.
 220 def _rgb_to_grayscale(images, name=None):
 221   """Converts one or more images from RGB to Grayscale.
 222 
 223   Outputs a tensor of the same `DType` and rank as `images`.  The size of the
 224   last dimension of the output is 1, containing the Grayscale value of the
 225   pixels.
 226 
 227   Args:
 228     images: The RGB tensor to convert. Last dimension must have size 3 and
 229       should contain RGB values.
 230     name: A name for the operation (optional).
 231 
 232   Returns:
 233     The converted grayscale image(s).
 234   """
 235   with tf.name_scope(name, 'rgb_to_grayscale', [images]) as name:
 236     images = tf.convert_to_tensor(images, name='images')
 237     # Remember original dtype to so we can convert back if needed
 238     orig_dtype = images.dtype
 239     flt_image = tf.image.convert_image_dtype(images, tf.float32)
 240 
 241     # Reference for converting between RGB and grayscale.
 242     # https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luma_%28video%29
 243     rgb_weights = [0.2989, 0.5870, 0.1140]
 244     rank_1 = tf.expand_dims(tf.rank(images) - 1, 0)
 245     gray_float = tf.reduce_sum(
 246         flt_image * rgb_weights, rank_1, keep_dims=True)
 247     gray_float.set_shape(images.get_shape()[:-1].concatenate([1]))
 248     return tf.image.convert_image_dtype(gray_float, orig_dtype, name=name)

 251 def normalize_image(image, original_minval, original_maxval, target_minval,
 252                     target_maxval):
 253   """Normalizes pixel values in the image.
 254 
 255   Moves the pixel values from the current [original_minval, original_maxval]
 256   range to a the [target_minval, target_maxval] range.
 257 
 258   Args:
 259     image: rank 3 float32 tensor containing 1
 260            image -> [height, width, channels].
 261     original_minval: current image minimum value.
 262     original_maxval: current image maximum value.
 263     target_minval: target image minimum value.
 264     target_maxval: target image maximum value.
 265 
 266   Returns:
 267     image: image which is the same shape as input image.
 268   """
 269   with tf.name_scope('NormalizeImage', values=[image]):
 270     original_minval = float(original_minval)
 271     original_maxval = float(original_maxval)
 272     target_minval = float(target_minval)
 273     target_maxval = float(target_maxval)
 274     image = tf.cast(image, dtype=tf.float32)
 275     image = tf.subtract(image, original_minval)
 276     image = tf.multiply(image, (target_maxval - target_minval) /
 277                         (original_maxval - original_minval))
 278     image = tf.add(image, target_minval)
 279     return image

 282 def retain_boxes_above_threshold(boxes,
 283                                  labels,
 284                                  label_weights,
 285                                  label_confidences=None,
 286                                  multiclass_scores=None,
 287                                  masks=None,
 288                                  keypoints=None,
 289                                  threshold=0.0):
 290   """Retains boxes whose label weight is above a given threshold.
 291 
 292   If the label weight for a box is missing (represented by NaN), the box is
 293   retained. The boxes that don't pass the threshold will not appear in the
 294   returned tensor.
 295 
 296   Args:
 297     boxes: float32 tensor of shape [num_instance, 4] representing boxes
 298       location in normalized coordinates.
 299     labels: rank 1 int32 tensor of shape [num_instance] containing the object
 300       classes.
 301     label_weights: float32 tensor of shape [num_instance] representing the
 302       weight for each box.
 303     label_confidences: float32 tensor of shape [num_instance] representing the
 304       confidence for each box.
 305     multiclass_scores: (optional) float32 tensor of shape
 306       [num_instances, num_classes] representing the score for each box for each
 307       class.
 308     masks: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 309       [num_instances, height, width] containing instance masks. The masks are of
 310       the same height, width as the input `image`.
 311     keypoints: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 312       [num_instances, num_keypoints, 2]. The keypoints are in y-x normalized
 313       coordinates.
 314     threshold: scalar python float.
 315 
 316   Returns:
 317     retained_boxes: [num_retained_instance, 4]
 318     retianed_labels: [num_retained_instance]
 319     retained_label_weights: [num_retained_instance]
 320 
 321     If multiclass_scores, masks, or keypoints are not None, the function also
 322       returns:
 323 
 324     retained_multiclass_scores: [num_retained_instance, num_classes]
 325     retained_masks: [num_retained_instance, height, width]
 326     retained_keypoints: [num_retained_instance, num_keypoints, 2]
 327   """
 328   with tf.name_scope('RetainBoxesAboveThreshold',
 329                      values=[boxes, labels, label_weights]):
 330     indices = tf.where(
 331         tf.logical_or(label_weights > threshold, tf.is_nan(label_weights)))
 332     indices = tf.squeeze(indices, axis=1)
 333     retained_boxes = tf.gather(boxes, indices)
 334     retained_labels = tf.gather(labels, indices)
 335     retained_label_weights = tf.gather(label_weights, indices)
 336     result = [retained_boxes, retained_labels, retained_label_weights]
 337 
 338     if label_confidences is not None:
 339       retained_label_confidences = tf.gather(label_confidences, indices)
 340       result.append(retained_label_confidences)
 341 
 342     if multiclass_scores is not None:
 343       retained_multiclass_scores = tf.gather(multiclass_scores, indices)
 344       result.append(retained_multiclass_scores)
 345 
 346     if masks is not None:
 347       retained_masks = tf.gather(masks, indices)
 348       result.append(retained_masks)
 349 
 350     if keypoints is not None:
 351       retained_keypoints = tf.gather(keypoints, indices)
 352       result.append(retained_keypoints)
 353 
 354     return result

 357 def drop_label_probabilistically(boxes,
 358                                  labels,
 359                                  label_weights,
 360                                  label_confidences=None,
 361                                  multiclass_scores=None,
 362                                  masks=None,
 363                                  keypoints=None,
 364                                  dropped_label=None,
 365                                  drop_probability=0.0,
 366                                  seed=None):
 367   """Drops boxes of a certain label with probability drop_probability.
 368 
 369   Boxes of the label dropped_label will not appear in the returned tensor.
 370 
 371   Args:
 372     boxes: float32 tensor of shape [num_instance, 4] representing boxes
 373       location in normalized coordinates.
 374     labels: rank 1 int32 tensor of shape [num_instance] containing the object
 375       classes.
 376     label_weights: float32 tensor of shape [num_instance] representing the
 377       weight for each box.
 378     label_confidences: float32 tensor of shape [num_instance] representing the
 379       confidence for each box.
 380     multiclass_scores: (optional) float32 tensor of shape
 381       [num_instances, num_classes] representing the score for each box for each
 382       class.
 383     masks: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 384       [num_instances, height, width] containing instance masks. The masks are of
 385       the same height, width as the input `image`.
 386     keypoints: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 387       [num_instances, num_keypoints, 2]. The keypoints are in y-x normalized
 388       coordinates.
 389     dropped_label: int32 id of label to drop.
 390     drop_probability: float32 probability of dropping a label.
 391     seed: random seed.
 392 
 393   Returns:
 394     retained_boxes: [num_retained_instance, 4]
 395     retianed_labels: [num_retained_instance]
 396     retained_label_weights: [num_retained_instance]
 397 
 398     If multiclass_scores, masks, or keypoints are not None, the function also
 399       returns:
 400 
 401     retained_multiclass_scores: [num_retained_instance, num_classes]
 402     retained_masks: [num_retained_instance, height, width]
 403     retained_keypoints: [num_retained_instance, num_keypoints, 2]
 404   """
 405   with tf.name_scope('DropLabelProbabilistically',
 406                      values=[boxes, labels]):
 407     indices = tf.where(
 408         tf.logical_or(
 409             tf.random_uniform(tf.shape(labels), seed=seed) > drop_probability,
 410             tf.not_equal(labels, dropped_label)))
 411     indices = tf.squeeze(indices, axis=1)
 412 
 413     retained_boxes = tf.gather(boxes, indices)
 414     retained_labels = tf.gather(labels, indices)
 415     retained_label_weights = tf.gather(label_weights, indices)
 416     result = [retained_boxes, retained_labels, retained_label_weights]
 417 
 418     if label_confidences is not None:
 419       retained_label_confidences = tf.gather(label_confidences, indices)
 420       result.append(retained_label_confidences)
 421 
 422     if multiclass_scores is not None:
 423       retained_multiclass_scores = tf.gather(multiclass_scores, indices)
 424       result.append(retained_multiclass_scores)
 425 
 426     if masks is not None:
 427       retained_masks = tf.gather(masks, indices)
 428       result.append(retained_masks)
 429 
 430     if keypoints is not None:
 431       retained_keypoints = tf.gather(keypoints, indices)
 432       result.append(retained_keypoints)
 433 
 434     return result

 437 def remap_labels(labels,
 438                  original_labels=None,
 439                  new_label=None):
 440   """Remaps labels that have an id in original_labels to new_label.
 441 
 442   Args:
 443     labels: rank 1 int32 tensor of shape [num_instance] containing the object
 444       classes.
 445       original_labels: int list of original labels that should be mapped from.
 446       new_label: int label to map to
 447   Returns:
 448     Remapped labels
 449   """
 450   new_labels = labels
 451   for original_label in original_labels:
 452     change = tf.where(
 453         tf.equal(new_labels, original_label),
 454         tf.add(tf.zeros_like(new_labels), new_label - original_label),
 455         tf.zeros_like(new_labels))
 456     new_labels = tf.add(
 457         new_labels,
 458         change)
 459   new_labels = tf.reshape(new_labels, tf.shape(labels))
 460   return new_labels

 463 def _flip_boxes_left_right(boxes):
 464   """Left-right flip the boxes.
 465 
 466   Args:
 467     boxes: Float32 tensor containing the bounding boxes -> [..., 4].
 468            Boxes are in normalized form meaning their coordinates vary
 469            between [0, 1].
 470            Each last dimension is in the form of [ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax].
 471 
 472   Returns:
 473     Flipped boxes.
 474   """
 475   ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax = tf.split(value=boxes, num_or_size_splits=4, axis=-1)
 476   flipped_xmin = tf.subtract(1.0, xmax)
 477   flipped_xmax = tf.subtract(1.0, xmin)
 478   flipped_boxes = tf.concat([ymin, flipped_xmin, ymax, flipped_xmax], axis=-1)
 479   return flipped_boxes
 480

 482 def _flip_boxes_up_down(boxes):
 483   """Up-down flip the boxes.
 484 
 485   Args:
 486     boxes: rank 2 float32 tensor containing the bounding boxes -> [N, 4].
 487            Boxes are in normalized form meaning their coordinates vary
 488            between [0, 1].
 489            Each row is in the form of [ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax].
 490 
 491   Returns:
 492     Flipped boxes.
 493   """
 494   ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax = tf.split(value=boxes, num_or_size_splits=4, axis=1)
 495   flipped_ymin = tf.subtract(1.0, ymax)
 496   flipped_ymax = tf.subtract(1.0, ymin)
 497   flipped_boxes = tf.concat([flipped_ymin, xmin, flipped_ymax, xmax], 1)
 498   return flipped_boxes

 501 def _rot90_boxes(boxes):
 502   """Rotate boxes counter-clockwise by 90 degrees.
 503 
 504   Args:
 505     boxes: rank 2 float32 tensor containing the bounding boxes -> [N, 4].
 506            Boxes are in normalized form meaning their coordinates vary
 507            between [0, 1].
 508            Each row is in the form of [ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax].
 509 
 510   Returns:
 511     Rotated boxes.
 512   """
 513   ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax = tf.split(value=boxes, num_or_size_splits=4, axis=1)
 514   rotated_ymin = tf.subtract(1.0, xmax)
 515   rotated_ymax = tf.subtract(1.0, xmin)
 516   rotated_xmin = ymin
 517   rotated_xmax = ymax
 518   rotated_boxes = tf.concat(
 519       [rotated_ymin, rotated_xmin, rotated_ymax, rotated_xmax], 1)
 520   return rotated_boxes

 523 def _flip_masks_left_right(masks):
 524   """Left-right flip masks.
 525 
 526   Args:
 527     masks: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 528       [num_instances, height, width] representing instance masks.
 529 
 530   Returns:
 531     flipped masks: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 532       [num_instances, height, width] representing instance masks.
 533   """
 534   return masks[:, :, ::-1]

 537 def _flip_masks_up_down(masks):

 539 
 540   Args:
 541     masks: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 542       [num_instances, height, width] representing instance masks.
 543 
 544   Returns:
 545     flipped masks: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 546       [num_instances, height, width] representing instance masks.
 547   """

 551 def _rot90_masks(masks):
 552   """Rotate masks counter-clockwise by 90 degrees.
 553 
 554   Args:
 555     masks: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 556       [num_instances, height, width] representing instance masks.
 557 
 558   Returns:
 559     rotated masks: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 560       [num_instances, height, width] representing instance masks.
 561   """
 562   masks = tf.transpose(masks, [0, 2, 1])
 563   return masks[:, ::-1, :]

 566 def random_horizontal_flip(image,
 567                            boxes=None,
 568                            masks=None,
 569                            keypoints=None,
 570                            keypoint_visibilities=None,
 571                            keypoint_flip_permutation=None,
 572                            seed=None,
 573                            preprocess_vars_cache=None):
 574   """Randomly flips the image and detections horizontally.
 575 
 576   The probability of flipping the image is 50%.
 577 
 578   Args:
 579     image: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape [height, width, channels].
 580     boxes: (optional) rank 2 float32 tensor with shape [N, 4]
 581            containing the bounding boxes.
 582            Boxes are in normalized form meaning their coordinates vary
 583            between [0, 1].
 584            Each row is in the form of [ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax].
 585     masks: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 586            [num_instances, height, width] containing instance masks. The masks
 587            are of the same height, width as the input `image`.
 588     keypoints: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 589                [num_instances, num_keypoints, 2]. The keypoints are in y-x
 590                normalized coordinates.
 591     keypoint_visibilities: (optional) rank 2 bool tensor with shape
 592                            [num_instances, num_keypoints].
 593     keypoint_flip_permutation: rank 1 int32 tensor containing the keypoint flip
 594                                permutation.
 595     seed: random seed
 596     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
 597                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
 598                            function is called multiple times with the same
 599                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
 600 
 601   Returns:
 602     image: image which is the same shape as input image.
 603 
 604     If boxes, masks, keypoints, keypoint_visibilities, and
 605     keypoint_flip_permutation are not None,the function also returns the
 606     following tensors.
 607 
 608     boxes: rank 2 float32 tensor containing the bounding boxes -> [N, 4].
 609            Boxes are in normalized form meaning their coordinates vary
 610            between [0, 1].
 611     masks: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape [num_instances, height, width]
 612            containing instance masks.
 613     keypoints: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 614                [num_instances, num_keypoints, 2]
 615     keypoint_visibilities: rank 2 bool tensor with shape
 616                            [num_instances, num_keypoints].
 617 
 618   Raises:
 619     ValueError: if keypoints are provided but keypoint_flip_permutation is not.
 620   """
 621 
 622   def _flip_image(image):
 623     # flip image
 624     image_flipped = tf.image.flip_left_right(image)
 625     return image_flipped
 626 
 627   if keypoints is not None and keypoint_flip_permutation is None:
 628     raise ValueError(
 629         'keypoints are provided but keypoints_flip_permutation is not provided')
 630 
 631   with tf.name_scope('RandomHorizontalFlip', values=[image, boxes]):
 632     result = []
 633     # random variable defining whether to do flip or not
 634     generator_func = functools.partial(tf.random_uniform, [], seed=seed)
 635     do_a_flip_random = _get_or_create_preprocess_rand_vars(
 636         generator_func,
 637         preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache.HORIZONTAL_FLIP,
 638         preprocess_vars_cache)
 639     do_a_flip_random = tf.greater(do_a_flip_random, 0.5)
 640 
 641     # flip image
 642     image = tf.cond(do_a_flip_random, lambda: _flip_image(image), lambda: image)
 643     result.append(image)
 644 
 645     # flip boxes
 646     if boxes is not None:
 647       boxes = tf.cond(do_a_flip_random, lambda: _flip_boxes_left_right(boxes),
 648                       lambda: boxes)
 649       result.append(boxes)
 650 
 651     # flip masks
 652     if masks is not None:
 653       masks = tf.cond(do_a_flip_random, lambda: _flip_masks_left_right(masks),
 654                       lambda: masks)
 655       result.append(masks)
 656 
 657     # flip keypoints
 658     if keypoints is not None and keypoint_flip_permutation is not None:
 659       permutation = keypoint_flip_permutation
 660       keypoints = tf.cond(
 661           do_a_flip_random,
 662           lambda: keypoint_ops.flip_horizontal(keypoints, 0.5, permutation),
 663           lambda: keypoints)
 664       result.append(keypoints)
 665 
 666     # flip keypoint visibilities
 667     if (keypoint_visibilities is not None and
 668         keypoint_flip_permutation is not None):
 669       permutation = keypoint_flip_permutation
 670       kpt_flip_perm = keypoint_flip_permutation
 671       keypoint_visibilities = tf.cond(
 672           do_a_flip_random,
 673           lambda: tf.gather(keypoint_visibilities, kpt_flip_perm, axis=1),
 674           lambda: keypoint_visibilities)
 675       result.append(keypoint_visibilities)
 676 
 677     return tuple(result)
 678

 776 def random_rotation90(image,
 777                       boxes=None,
 778                       masks=None,
 779                       keypoints=None,
 780                       seed=None,
 781                       preprocess_vars_cache=None):
 782   """Randomly rotates the image and detections 90 degrees counter-clockwise.
 783 
 784   The probability of rotating the image is 50%. This can be combined with
 785   random_horizontal_flip and random_vertical_flip to produce an output with a
 786   uniform distribution of the eight possible 90 degree rotation / reflection
 787   combinations.
 788 
 789   Args:
 790     image: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape [height, width, channels].
 791     boxes: (optional) rank 2 float32 tensor with shape [N, 4]
 792            containing the bounding boxes.
 793            Boxes are in normalized form meaning their coordinates vary
 794            between [0, 1].
 795            Each row is in the form of [ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax].
 796     masks: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 797            [num_instances, height, width] containing instance masks. The masks
 798            are of the same height, width as the input `image`.
 799     keypoints: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 800                [num_instances, num_keypoints, 2]. The keypoints are in y-x
 801                normalized coordinates.
 802     seed: random seed
 803     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
 804                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
 805                            function is called multiple times with the same
 806                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
 807 
 808   Returns:
 809     image: image which is the same shape as input image.
 810 
 811     If boxes, masks, and keypoints, are not None,
 812     the function also returns the following tensors.
 813 
 814     boxes: rank 2 float32 tensor containing the bounding boxes -> [N, 4].
 815            Boxes are in normalized form meaning their coordinates vary
 816            between [0, 1].
 817     masks: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape [num_instances, height, width]
 818            containing instance masks.
 819     keypoints: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
 820                [num_instances, num_keypoints, 2]
 821   """
 822 
 823   def _rot90_image(image):
 824     # flip image
 825     image_rotated = tf.image.rot90(image)
 826     return image_rotated
 827 
 828   with tf.name_scope('RandomRotation90', values=[image, boxes]):
 829     result = []
 830 
 831     # random variable defining whether to rotate by 90 degrees or not
 832     generator_func = functools.partial(tf.random_uniform, [], seed=seed)
 833     do_a_rot90_random = _get_or_create_preprocess_rand_vars(
 834         generator_func, preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache.ROTATION90,
 835         preprocess_vars_cache)
 836     do_a_rot90_random = tf.greater(do_a_rot90_random, 0.5)
 837 
 838     # flip image
 839     image = tf.cond(do_a_rot90_random, lambda: _rot90_image(image),
 840                     lambda: image)
 841     result.append(image)
 842 
 843     # flip boxes
 844     if boxes is not None:
 845       boxes = tf.cond(do_a_rot90_random, lambda: _rot90_boxes(boxes),
 846                       lambda: boxes)
 847       result.append(boxes)
 848 
 849     # flip masks
 850     if masks is not None:
 851       masks = tf.cond(do_a_rot90_random, lambda: _rot90_masks(masks),
 852                       lambda: masks)
 853       result.append(masks)
 854 
 855     # flip keypoints
 856     if keypoints is not None:
 857       keypoints = tf.cond(
 858           do_a_rot90_random,
 859           lambda: keypoint_ops.rot90(keypoints),
 860           lambda: keypoints)
 861       result.append(keypoints)
 862 
 863     return tuple(result)

 866 def random_pixel_value_scale(image,
 867                              minval=0.9,
 868                              maxval=1.1,
 869                              seed=None,
 870                              preprocess_vars_cache=None):
 871   """Scales each value in the pixels of the image.
 872 
 873      This function scales each pixel independent of the other ones.
 874      For each value in image tensor, draws a random number between
 875      minval and maxval and multiples the values with them.
 876 
 877   Args:
 878     image: rank 3 float32 tensor contains 1 image -> [height, width, channels]
 879            with pixel values varying between [0, 255].
 880     minval: lower ratio of scaling pixel values.
 881     maxval: upper ratio of scaling pixel values.
 882     seed: random seed.
 883     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
 884                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
 885                            function is called multiple times with the same
 886                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
 887 
 888   Returns:
 889     image: image which is the same shape as input image.
 890   """
 891   with tf.name_scope('RandomPixelValueScale', values=[image]):
 892     generator_func = functools.partial(
 893         tf.random_uniform, tf.shape(image),
 894         minval=minval, maxval=maxval,
 895         dtype=tf.float32, seed=seed)
 896     color_coef = _get_or_create_preprocess_rand_vars(
 897         generator_func,
 898         preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache.PIXEL_VALUE_SCALE,
 899         preprocess_vars_cache)
 900 
 901     image = tf.multiply(image, color_coef)
 902     image = tf.clip_by_value(image, 0.0, 255.0)
 903 
 904   return image

 907 def random_image_scale(image,
 908                        masks=None,
 909                        min_scale_ratio=0.5,
 910                        max_scale_ratio=2.0,
 911                        seed=None,
 912                        preprocess_vars_cache=None):
 913   """Scales the image size.
 914 
 915   Args:
 916     image: rank 3 float32 tensor contains 1 image -> [height, width, channels].
 917     masks: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor containing masks with
 918       size [height, width, num_masks]. The value is set to None if there are no
 919       masks.
 920     min_scale_ratio: minimum scaling ratio.
 921     max_scale_ratio: maximum scaling ratio.
 922     seed: random seed.
 923     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
 924                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
 925                            function is called multiple times with the same
 926                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
 927 
 928   Returns:
 929     image: image which is the same rank as input image.
 930     masks: If masks is not none, resized masks which are the same rank as input
 931       masks will be returned.
 932   """
 933   with tf.name_scope('RandomImageScale', values=[image]):
 934     result = []
 935     image_shape = tf.shape(image)
 936     image_height = image_shape[0]
 937     image_width = image_shape[1]
 938     generator_func = functools.partial(
 939         tf.random_uniform, [],
 940         minval=min_scale_ratio, maxval=max_scale_ratio,
 941         dtype=tf.float32, seed=seed)
 942     size_coef = _get_or_create_preprocess_rand_vars(
 943         generator_func, preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache.IMAGE_SCALE,
 944         preprocess_vars_cache)
 945 
 946     image_newysize = tf.cast(
 947         tf.multiply(tf.cast(image_height, dtype=tf.float32), size_coef),
 948         dtype=tf.int32)
 949     image_newxsize = tf.cast(
 950         tf.multiply(tf.cast(image_width, dtype=tf.float32), size_coef),
 951         dtype=tf.int32)
 952     image = tf.image.resize_images(
 953         image, [image_newysize, image_newxsize], align_corners=True)
 954     result.append(image)
 955     if masks is not None:
 956       masks = tf.image.resize_images(
 957           masks, [image_newysize, image_newxsize],
 958           method=tf.image.ResizeMethod.NEAREST_NEIGHBOR,
 959           align_corners=True)
 960       result.append(masks)
 961     return tuple(result)
 962

 964 def _augment_only_rgb_channels(image, augment_function):
 965   """Augments only the RGB slice of an image with additional channels."""
 966   rgb_slice = image[:, :, :3]
 967   augmented_rgb_slice = augment_function(rgb_slice)
 968   image = tf.concat([augmented_rgb_slice, image[:, :, 3:]], -1)
 969   return image

 972 def random_rgb_to_gray(image,
 973                        probability=0.1,
 974                        seed=None,
 975                        preprocess_vars_cache=None):
 976   """Changes the image from RGB to Grayscale with the given probability.
 977 
 978   Args:
 979     image: rank 3 float32 tensor contains 1 image -> [height, width, channels]
 980            with pixel values varying between [0, 255].
 981     probability: the probability of returning a grayscale image.
 982             The probability should be a number between [0, 1].
 983     seed: random seed.
 984     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
 985                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
 986                            function is called multiple times with the same
 987                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
 988 
 989   Returns:
 990     image: image which is the same shape as input image.
 991   """
 992   def _image_to_gray(image):
 993     image_gray1 = _rgb_to_grayscale(image)
 994     image_gray3 = tf.image.grayscale_to_rgb(image_gray1)
 995     return image_gray3
 996 
 997   with tf.name_scope('RandomRGBtoGray', values=[image]):
 998     # random variable defining whether to change to grayscale or not
 999     generator_func = functools.partial(tf.random_uniform, [], seed=seed)
1000     do_gray_random = _get_or_create_preprocess_rand_vars(
1001         generator_func, preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache.RGB_TO_GRAY,
1002         preprocess_vars_cache)
1003 
1004     image = tf.cond(
1005         tf.greater(do_gray_random, probability), lambda: image,
1006         lambda: _augment_only_rgb_channels(image, _image_to_gray))
1007 
1008   return image

1011 def random_adjust_brightness(image,
1012                              max_delta=0.2,
1013                              seed=None,
1014                              preprocess_vars_cache=None):
1015   """Randomly adjusts brightness.
1016 
1017   Makes sure the output image is still between 0 and 255.
1018 
1019   Args:
1020     image: rank 3 float32 tensor contains 1 image -> [height, width, channels]
1021            with pixel values varying between [0, 255].
1022     max_delta: how much to change the brightness. A value between [0, 1).
1023     seed: random seed.
1024     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
1025                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
1026                            function is called multiple times with the same
1027                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
1028 
1029   Returns:
1030     image: image which is the same shape as input image.
1031     boxes: boxes which is the same shape as input boxes.
1032   """
1033   with tf.name_scope('RandomAdjustBrightness', values=[image]):
1034     generator_func = functools.partial(tf.random_uniform, [],
1035                                        -max_delta, max_delta, seed=seed)
1036     delta = _get_or_create_preprocess_rand_vars(
1037         generator_func,
1038         preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache.ADJUST_BRIGHTNESS,
1039         preprocess_vars_cache)
1040 
1041     def _adjust_brightness(image):
1042       image = tf.image.adjust_brightness(image / 255, delta) * 255
1043       image = tf.clip_by_value(image, clip_value_min=0.0, clip_value_max=255.0)
1044       return image
1045 
1046     image = _augment_only_rgb_channels(image, _adjust_brightness)
1047     return image

1158     def _adjust_saturation(image):
1159       image = tf.image.adjust_saturation(image / 255, saturation_factor) * 255
1160       image = tf.clip_by_value(image, clip_value_min=0.0, clip_value_max=255.0)
1161       return image
1162     image = _augment_only_rgb_channels(image, _adjust_saturation)
1163     return image
1164

1166 def random_distort_color(image, color_ordering=0, preprocess_vars_cache=None):
1167   """Randomly distorts color.
1168 
1169   Randomly distorts color using a combination of brightness, hue, contrast and
1170   saturation changes. Makes sure the output image is still between 0 and 255.
1171 
1172   Args:
1173     image: rank 3 float32 tensor contains 1 image -> [height, width, channels]
1174            with pixel values varying between [0, 255].
1175     color_ordering: Python int, a type of distortion (valid values: 0, 1).
1176     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
1177                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
1178                            function is called multiple times with the same
1179                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
1180 
1181   Returns:
1182     image: image which is the same shape as input image.
1183 
1184   Raises:
1185     ValueError: if color_ordering is not in {0, 1}.
1186   """
1187   with tf.name_scope('RandomDistortColor', values=[image]):
1188     if color_ordering == 0:
1189       image = random_adjust_brightness(
1190           image, max_delta=32. / 255.,
1191           preprocess_vars_cache=preprocess_vars_cache)
1192       image = random_adjust_saturation(
1193           image, min_delta=0.5, max_delta=1.5,
1194           preprocess_vars_cache=preprocess_vars_cache)
1195       image = random_adjust_hue(
1196           image, max_delta=0.2,
1197           preprocess_vars_cache=preprocess_vars_cache)
1198       image = random_adjust_contrast(
1199           image, min_delta=0.5, max_delta=1.5,
1200           preprocess_vars_cache=preprocess_vars_cache)
1201 
1202     elif color_ordering == 1:
1203       image = random_adjust_brightness(
1204           image, max_delta=32. / 255.,
1205           preprocess_vars_cache=preprocess_vars_cache)
1206       image = random_adjust_contrast(
1207           image, min_delta=0.5, max_delta=1.5,
1208           preprocess_vars_cache=preprocess_vars_cache)
1209       image = random_adjust_saturation(
1210           image, min_delta=0.5, max_delta=1.5,
1211           preprocess_vars_cache=preprocess_vars_cache)
1212       image = random_adjust_hue(
1213           image, max_delta=0.2,
1214           preprocess_vars_cache=preprocess_vars_cache)
1215     else:
1216       raise ValueError('color_ordering must be in {0, 1}')
1217     return image

1220 def random_jitter_boxes(boxes, ratio=0.05, seed=None):
1221   """Randomly jitter boxes in image.
1222 
1223   Args:
1224     boxes: rank 2 float32 tensor containing the bounding boxes -> [N, 4].
1225            Boxes are in normalized form meaning their coordinates vary
1226            between [0, 1].
1227            Each row is in the form of [ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax].
1228     ratio: The ratio of the box width and height that the corners can jitter.
1229            For example if the width is 100 pixels and ratio is 0.05,
1230            the corners can jitter up to 5 pixels in the x direction.
1231     seed: random seed.
1232 
1233   Returns:
1234     boxes: boxes which is the same shape as input boxes.
1235   """
1236   def random_jitter_box(box, ratio, seed):
1237     """Randomly jitter box.
1238 
1239     Args:
1240       box: bounding box [1, 1, 4].
1241       ratio: max ratio between jittered box and original box,
1242       a number between [0, 0.5].
1243       seed: random seed.
1244 
1245     Returns:
1246       jittered_box: jittered box.
1247     """
1248     rand_numbers = tf.random_uniform(
1249         [1, 1, 4], minval=-ratio, maxval=ratio, dtype=tf.float32, seed=seed)
1250     box_width = tf.subtract(box[0, 0, 3], box[0, 0, 1])
1251     box_height = tf.subtract(box[0, 0, 2], box[0, 0, 0])
1252     hw_coefs = tf.stack([box_height, box_width, box_height, box_width])
1253     hw_rand_coefs = tf.multiply(hw_coefs, rand_numbers)
1254     jittered_box = tf.add(box, hw_rand_coefs)
1255     jittered_box = tf.clip_by_value(jittered_box, 0.0, 1.0)
1256     return jittered_box
1257 
1258   with tf.name_scope('RandomJitterBoxes', values=[boxes]):
1259     # boxes are [N, 4]. Lets first make them [N, 1, 1, 4]
1260     boxes_shape = tf.shape(boxes)
1261     boxes = tf.expand_dims(boxes, 1)
1262     boxes = tf.expand_dims(boxes, 2)
1263 
1264     distorted_boxes = tf.map_fn(
1265         lambda x: random_jitter_box(x, ratio, seed), boxes, dtype=tf.float32)
1266 
1267     distorted_boxes = tf.reshape(distorted_boxes, boxes_shape)
1268 
1269     return distorted_boxes
1270

1272 def _strict_random_crop_image(image,
1273                               boxes,
1274                               labels,
1275                               label_weights,
1276                               label_confidences=None,
1277                               multiclass_scores=None,
1278                               masks=None,
1279                               keypoints=None,
1280                               keypoint_visibilities=None,
1281                               min_object_covered=1.0,
1282                               aspect_ratio_range=(0.75, 1.33),
1283                               area_range=(0.1, 1.0),
1284                               overlap_thresh=0.3,
1285                               clip_boxes=True,
1286                               preprocess_vars_cache=None):
1287   """Performs random crop.
1288 
1289   Note: Keypoint coordinates that are outside the crop will be set to NaN, which
1290   is consistent with the original keypoint encoding for non-existing keypoints.
1291   This function always crops the image and is supposed to be used by
1292   `random_crop_image` function which sometimes returns the image unchanged.
1293 
1294   Args:
1295     image: rank 3 float32 tensor containing 1 image -> [height, width, channels]
1296            with pixel values varying between [0, 1].
1297     boxes: rank 2 float32 tensor containing the bounding boxes with shape
1298            [num_instances, 4].
1299            Boxes are in normalized form meaning their coordinates vary
1300            between [0, 1].
1301            Each row is in the form of [ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax].
1302     labels: rank 1 int32 tensor containing the object classes.
1303     label_weights: float32 tensor of shape [num_instances] representing the
1304       weight for each box.
1305     label_confidences: (optional) float32 tensor of shape [num_instances]
1306       representing the confidence for each box.
1307     multiclass_scores: (optional) float32 tensor of shape
1308       [num_instances, num_classes] representing the score for each box for each
1309       class.
1310     masks: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
1311            [num_instances, height, width] containing instance masks. The masks
1312            are of the same height, width as the input `image`.
1313     keypoints: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
1314                [num_instances, num_keypoints, 2]. The keypoints are in y-x
1315                normalized coordinates.
1316     keypoint_visibilities: (optional) rank 2 bool tensor with shape
1317                [num_instances, num_keypoints].
1318     min_object_covered: the cropped image must cover at least this fraction of
1319                         at least one of the input bounding boxes.
1320     aspect_ratio_range: allowed range for aspect ratio of cropped image.
1321     area_range: allowed range for area ratio between cropped image and the
1322                 original image.
1323     overlap_thresh: minimum overlap thresh with new cropped
1324                     image to keep the box.
1325     clip_boxes: whether to clip the boxes to the cropped image.
1326     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
1327                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
1328                            function is called multiple times with the same
1329                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
1330 
1331   Returns:
1332     image: image which is the same rank as input image.
1333     boxes: boxes which is the same rank as input boxes.
1334            Boxes are in normalized form.
1335     labels: new labels.
1336 
1337     If label_weights, multiclass_scores, masks, keypoints, or
1338     keypoint_visibilities is not None, the function also returns:
1339     label_weights: rank 1 float32 tensor with shape [num_instances].
1340     multiclass_scores: rank 2 float32 tensor with shape
1341                        [num_instances, num_classes]
1342     masks: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape [num_instances, height, width]
1343            containing instance masks.
1344     keypoints: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
1345                [num_instances, num_keypoints, 2]
1346     keypoint_visibilities: rank 2 bool tensor with shape
1347                [num_instances, num_keypoints]
1348   """
1349   with tf.name_scope('RandomCropImage', values=[image, boxes]):
1350     image_shape = tf.shape(image)
1351 
1352     # boxes are [N, 4]. Lets first make them [N, 1, 4].
1353     boxes_expanded = tf.expand_dims(
1354         tf.clip_by_value(
1355             boxes, clip_value_min=0.0, clip_value_max=1.0), 1)
1356 
1357     generator_func = functools.partial(
1358         tf.image.sample_distorted_bounding_box,
1359         image_shape,
1360         bounding_boxes=boxes_expanded,
1361         min_object_covered=min_object_covered,
1362         aspect_ratio_range=aspect_ratio_range,
1363         area_range=area_range,
1364         max_attempts=100,
1365         use_image_if_no_bounding_boxes=True)
1366 
1367     # for ssd cropping, each value of min_object_covered has its own
1368     # cached random variable
1369     sample_distorted_bounding_box = _get_or_create_preprocess_rand_vars(
1370         generator_func,
1371         preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache.STRICT_CROP_IMAGE,
1372         preprocess_vars_cache, key=min_object_covered)
1373 
1374     im_box_begin, im_box_size, im_box = sample_distorted_bounding_box
1375     im_box_end = im_box_begin + im_box_size
1376     new_image = image[im_box_begin[0]:im_box_end[0],
1377                       im_box_begin[1]:im_box_end[1], :]
1378     new_image.set_shape([None, None, image.get_shape()[2]])
1379 
1380     # [1, 4]
1381     im_box_rank2 = tf.squeeze(im_box, axis=[0])
1382     # [4]
1383     im_box_rank1 = tf.squeeze(im_box)
1384 
1385     boxlist = box_list.BoxList(boxes)
1386     boxlist.add_field('labels', labels)
1387 
1388     if label_weights is not None:
1389       boxlist.add_field('label_weights', label_weights)
1390 
1391     if label_confidences is not None:
1392       boxlist.add_field('label_confidences', label_confidences)
1393 
1394     if multiclass_scores is not None:
1395       boxlist.add_field('multiclass_scores', multiclass_scores)
1396 
1397     im_boxlist = box_list.BoxList(im_box_rank2)
1398 
1399     # remove boxes that are outside cropped image
1400     boxlist, inside_window_ids = box_list_ops.prune_completely_outside_window(
1401         boxlist, im_box_rank1)
1402 
1403     # remove boxes that are outside image
1404     overlapping_boxlist, keep_ids = box_list_ops.prune_non_overlapping_boxes(
1405         boxlist, im_boxlist, overlap_thresh)
1406 
1407     # change the coordinate of the remaining boxes
1408     new_labels = overlapping_boxlist.get_field('labels')
1409     new_boxlist = box_list_ops.change_coordinate_frame(overlapping_boxlist,
1410                                                        im_box_rank1)
1411     new_boxes = new_boxlist.get()
1412     if clip_boxes:
1413       new_boxes = tf.clip_by_value(
1414           new_boxes, clip_value_min=0.0, clip_value_max=1.0)
1415 
1416     result = [new_image, new_boxes, new_labels]
1417 
1418     if label_weights is not None:
1419       new_label_weights = overlapping_boxlist.get_field('label_weights')
1420       result.append(new_label_weights)
1421 
1422     if label_confidences is not None:
1423       new_label_confidences = overlapping_boxlist.get_field('label_confidences')
1424       result.append(new_label_confidences)
1425 
1426     if multiclass_scores is not None:
1427       new_multiclass_scores = overlapping_boxlist.get_field('multiclass_scores')
1428       result.append(new_multiclass_scores)
1429 
1430     if masks is not None:
1431       masks_of_boxes_inside_window = tf.gather(masks, inside_window_ids)
1432       masks_of_boxes_completely_inside_window = tf.gather(
1433           masks_of_boxes_inside_window, keep_ids)
1434       new_masks = masks_of_boxes_completely_inside_window[:, im_box_begin[
1435           0]:im_box_end[0], im_box_begin[1]:im_box_end[1]]
1436       result.append(new_masks)
1437 
1438     if keypoints is not None:
1439       keypoints_of_boxes_inside_window = tf.gather(keypoints, inside_window_ids)
1440       keypoints_of_boxes_completely_inside_window = tf.gather(
1441           keypoints_of_boxes_inside_window, keep_ids)
1442       new_keypoints = keypoint_ops.change_coordinate_frame(
1443           keypoints_of_boxes_completely_inside_window, im_box_rank1)
1444       if clip_boxes:
1445         new_keypoints = keypoint_ops.prune_outside_window(new_keypoints,
1446                                                           [0.0, 0.0, 1.0, 1.0])
1447       result.append(new_keypoints)
1448 
1449     if keypoint_visibilities is not None:
1450       kpt_vis_of_boxes_inside_window = tf.gather(keypoint_visibilities,
1451                                                  inside_window_ids)
1452       kpt_vis_of_boxes_completely_inside_window = tf.gather(
1453           kpt_vis_of_boxes_inside_window, keep_ids)
1454       if clip_boxes:
1455         # Set any keypoints with NaN coordinates to invisible.
1456         new_kpt_visibilities = keypoint_ops.set_keypoint_visibilities(
1457             new_keypoints, kpt_vis_of_boxes_completely_inside_window)
1458         result.append(new_kpt_visibilities)
1459 
1460     return tuple(result)
1461 
1462 
1463 def random_crop_image(image,
1464                       boxes,
1465                       labels,
1466                       label_weights,
1467                       label_confidences=None,
1468                       multiclass_scores=None,
1469                       masks=None,
1470                       keypoints=None,
1471                       keypoint_visibilities=None,
1472                       min_object_covered=1.0,
1473                       aspect_ratio_range=(0.75, 1.33),
1474                       area_range=(0.1, 1.0),
1475                       overlap_thresh=0.3,
1476                       clip_boxes=True,
1477                       random_coef=0.0,
1478                       seed=None,
1479                       preprocess_vars_cache=None):
1480   """Randomly crops the image.
1481 
1482   Given the input image and its bounding boxes, this op randomly
1483   crops a subimage.  Given a user-provided set of input constraints,
1484   the crop window is resampled until it satisfies these constraints.
1485   If within 100 trials it is unable to find a valid crop, the original
1486   image is returned. See the Args section for a description of the input
1487   constraints. Both input boxes and returned Boxes are in normalized
1488   form (e.g., lie in the unit square [0, 1]).
1489   This function will return the original image with probability random_coef.
1490 
1491   Note: Keypoint coordinates that are outside the crop will be set to NaN, which
1492   is consistent with the original keypoint encoding for non-existing keypoints.
1493   Also, the keypoint visibility will be set to False.
1494 
1495   Args:
1496     image: rank 3 float32 tensor contains 1 image -> [height, width, channels]
1497            with pixel values varying between [0, 1].
1498     boxes: rank 2 float32 tensor containing the bounding boxes with shape
1499            [num_instances, 4].
1500            Boxes are in normalized form meaning their coordinates vary
1501            between [0, 1].
1502            Each row is in the form of [ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax].
1503     labels: rank 1 int32 tensor containing the object classes.
1504     label_weights: float32 tensor of shape [num_instances] representing the
1505       weight for each box.
1506     label_confidences: (optional) float32 tensor of shape [num_instances].
1507       representing the confidence for each box.
1508     multiclass_scores: (optional) float32 tensor of shape
1509       [num_instances, num_classes] representing the score for each box for each
1510       class.
1511     masks: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
1512            [num_instances, height, width] containing instance masks. The masks
1513            are of the same height, width as the input `image`.
1514     keypoints: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
1515                [num_instances, num_keypoints, 2]. The keypoints are in y-x
1516                normalized coordinates.
1517     keypoint_visibilities: (optional) rank 2 bool tensor with shape
1518                            [num_instances, num_keypoints].
1519     min_object_covered: the cropped image must cover at least this fraction of
1520                         at least one of the input bounding boxes.
1521     aspect_ratio_range: allowed range for aspect ratio of cropped image.
1522     area_range: allowed range for area ratio between cropped image and the
1523                 original image.
1524     overlap_thresh: minimum overlap thresh with new cropped
1525                     image to keep the box.
1526     clip_boxes: whether to clip the boxes to the cropped image.
1527     random_coef: a random coefficient that defines the chance of getting the
1528                  original image. If random_coef is 0, we will always get the
1529                  cropped image, and if it is 1.0, we will always get the
1530                  original image.
1531     seed: random seed.
1532     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
1533                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
1534                            function is called multiple times with the same
1535                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
1536 
1537   Returns:
1538     image: Image shape will be [new_height, new_width, channels].
1539     boxes: boxes which is the same rank as input boxes. Boxes are in normalized
1540            form.
1541     labels: new labels.
1542 
1543     If label_weights, multiclass_scores, masks, keypoints, keypoint_visibilities
1544     is not None, the function also returns:
1545     label_weights: rank 1 float32 tensor with shape [num_instances].
1546     multiclass_scores: rank 2 float32 tensor with shape
1547                        [num_instances, num_classes]
1548     masks: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape [num_instances, height, width]
1549            containing instance masks.
1550     keypoints: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
1551                [num_instances, num_keypoints, 2]
1552     keypoint_visibilities: rank 2 bool tensor with shape
1553                [num_instances, num_keypoints]
1554   """
1555 
1556   def strict_random_crop_image_fn():
1557     return _strict_random_crop_image(
1558         image,
1559         boxes,
1560         labels,
1561         label_weights,
1562         label_confidences=label_confidences,
1563         multiclass_scores=multiclass_scores,
1564         masks=masks,
1565         keypoints=keypoints,
1566         keypoint_visibilities=keypoint_visibilities,
1567         min_object_covered=min_object_covered,
1568         aspect_ratio_range=aspect_ratio_range,
1569         area_range=area_range,
1570         overlap_thresh=overlap_thresh,
1571         clip_boxes=clip_boxes,
1572         preprocess_vars_cache=preprocess_vars_cache)
1573 
1574   # avoids tf.cond to make faster RCNN training on borg. See b/140057645.
1575   if random_coef < sys.float_info.min:
1576     result = strict_random_crop_image_fn()
1577   else:
1578     generator_func = functools.partial(tf.random_uniform, [], seed=seed)
1579     do_a_crop_random = _get_or_create_preprocess_rand_vars(
1580         generator_func, preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache.CROP_IMAGE,
1581         preprocess_vars_cache)
1582     do_a_crop_random = tf.greater(do_a_crop_random, random_coef)
1583 
1584     outputs = [image, boxes, labels]
1585 
1586     if label_weights is not None:
1587       outputs.append(label_weights)
1588     if label_confidences is not None:
1589       outputs.append(label_confidences)
1590     if multiclass_scores is not None:
1591       outputs.append(multiclass_scores)
1592     if masks is not None:
1593       outputs.append(masks)
1594     if keypoints is not None:
1595       outputs.append(keypoints)
1596     if keypoint_visibilities is not None:
1597       outputs.append(keypoint_visibilities)
1598 
1599     result = tf.cond(do_a_crop_random, strict_random_crop_image_fn,
1600                      lambda: tuple(outputs))
1601   return result
1602 
1603 
1604 def random_pad_image(image,
1605                      boxes,
1606                      masks=None,
1607                      keypoints=None,
1608                      min_image_size=None,
1609                      max_image_size=None,
1610                      pad_color=None,
1611                      seed=None,
1612                      preprocess_vars_cache=None):
1613   """Randomly pads the image.
1614 
1615   This function randomly pads the image with zeros. The final size of the
1616   padded image will be between min_image_size and max_image_size.
1617   if min_image_size is smaller than the input image size, min_image_size will
1618   be set to the input image size. The same for max_image_size. The input image
1619   will be located at a uniformly random location inside the padded image.
1620   The relative location of the boxes to the original image will remain the same.
1621 
1622   Args:
1623     image: rank 3 float32 tensor containing 1 image -> [height, width, channels]
1624            with pixel values varying between [0, 1].
1625     boxes: rank 2 float32 tensor containing the bounding boxes -> [N, 4].
1626            Boxes are in normalized form meaning their coordinates vary
1627            between [0, 1].
1628            Each row is in the form of [ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax].
1629     masks: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
1630            [N, height, width] containing instance masks. The masks
1631            are of the same height, width as the input `image`.
1632     keypoints: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
1633                [N, num_keypoints, 2]. The keypoints are in y-x normalized
1634                coordinates.
1635     min_image_size: a tensor of size [min_height, min_width], type tf.int32.
1636                     If passed as None, will be set to image size
1637                     [height, width].
1638     max_image_size: a tensor of size [max_height, max_width], type tf.int32.
1639                     If passed as None, will be set to twice the
1640                     image [height * 2, width * 2].
1641     pad_color: padding color. A rank 1 tensor of [channels] with dtype=
1642                tf.float32. if set as None, it will be set to average color of
1643                the input image.
1644     seed: random seed.
1645     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
1646                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
1647                            function is called multiple times with the same
1648                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
1649 
1650   Returns:
1651     image: Image shape will be [new_height, new_width, channels].
1652     boxes: boxes which is the same rank as input boxes. Boxes are in normalized
1653            form.
1654 
1655     if masks is not None, the function also returns:
1656     masks: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape [N, new_height, new_width]
1657     if keypoints is not None, the function also returns:
1658     keypoints: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape [N, num_keypoints, 2]
1659   """
1660   if pad_color is None:
1661     pad_color = tf.reduce_mean(image, axis=[0, 1])
1662 
1663   image_shape = tf.shape(image)
1664   image_height = image_shape[0]
1665   image_width = image_shape[1]
1666 
1667   if max_image_size is None:
1668     max_image_size = tf.stack([image_height * 2, image_width * 2])
1669   max_image_size = tf.maximum(max_image_size,
1670                               tf.stack([image_height, image_width]))
1671 
1672   if min_image_size is None:
1673     min_image_size = tf.stack([image_height, image_width])
1674   min_image_size = tf.maximum(min_image_size,
1675                               tf.stack([image_height, image_width]))
1676 
1677   target_height = tf.cond(
1678       max_image_size[0] > min_image_size[0],
1679       lambda: _random_integer(min_image_size[0], max_image_size[0], seed),
1680       lambda: max_image_size[0])
1681 
1682   target_width = tf.cond(
1683       max_image_size[1] > min_image_size[1],
1684       lambda: _random_integer(min_image_size[1], max_image_size[1], seed),
1685       lambda: max_image_size[1])
1686 
1687   offset_height = tf.cond(
1688       target_height > image_height,
1689       lambda: _random_integer(0, target_height - image_height, seed),
1690       lambda: tf.constant(0, dtype=tf.int32))
1691 
1692   offset_width = tf.cond(
1693       target_width > image_width,
1694       lambda: _random_integer(0, target_width - image_width, seed),
1695       lambda: tf.constant(0, dtype=tf.int32))
1696 
1697   gen_func = lambda: (target_height, target_width, offset_height, offset_width)
1698   params = _get_or_create_preprocess_rand_vars(
1699       gen_func, preprocessor_cache.PreprocessorCache.PAD_IMAGE,
1700       preprocess_vars_cache)
1701   target_height, target_width, offset_height, offset_width = params
1702 
1703   new_image = tf.image.pad_to_bounding_box(
1704       image,
1705       offset_height=offset_height,
1706       offset_width=offset_width,
1707       target_height=target_height,
1708       target_width=target_width)
1709 
1710   # Setting color of the padded pixels
1711   image_ones = tf.ones_like(image)
1712   image_ones_padded = tf.image.pad_to_bounding_box(
1713       image_ones,
1714       offset_height=offset_height,
1715       offset_width=offset_width,
1716       target_height=target_height,
1717       target_width=target_width)
1718   image_color_padded = (1.0 - image_ones_padded) * pad_color
1719   new_image += image_color_padded
1720 
1721   # setting boxes
1722   new_window = tf.cast(
1723       tf.stack([
1724           -offset_height, -offset_width, target_height - offset_height,
1725           target_width - offset_width
1726       ]),
1727       dtype=tf.float32)
1728   new_window /= tf.cast(
1729       tf.stack([image_height, image_width, image_height, image_width]),
1730       dtype=tf.float32)
1731   boxlist = box_list.BoxList(boxes)
1732   new_boxlist = box_list_ops.change_coordinate_frame(boxlist, new_window)
1733   new_boxes = new_boxlist.get()
1734 
1735   result = [new_image, new_boxes]
1736 
1737   if masks is not None:
1738     new_masks = tf.image.pad_to_bounding_box(
1739         masks[:, :, :, tf.newaxis],
1740         offset_height=offset_height,
1741         offset_width=offset_width,
1742         target_height=target_height,
1743         target_width=target_width)[:, :, :, 0]
1744     result.append(new_masks)
1745 
1746   if keypoints is not None:
1747     new_keypoints = keypoint_ops.change_coordinate_frame(keypoints, new_window)
1748     result.append(new_keypoints)
1749 
1750   return tuple(result)
1751

1753 def random_absolute_pad_image(image,
1754                               boxes,
1755                               masks=None,
1756                               keypoints=None,
1757                               max_height_padding=None,
1758                               max_width_padding=None,
1759                               pad_color=None,
1760                               seed=None,
1761                               preprocess_vars_cache=None):
1762   """Randomly pads the image by small absolute amounts.
1763 
1764   As random_pad_image above, but the padding is of size [0, max_height_padding]
1765   or [0, max_width_padding] instead of padding to a fixed size of
1766   max_height_padding for all images.
1767 
1768   Args:
1769     image: rank 3 float32 tensor containing 1 image -> [height, width, channels]
1770            with pixel values varying between [0, 1].
1771     boxes: rank 2 float32 tensor containing the bounding boxes -> [N, 4].
1772            Boxes are in normalized form meaning their coordinates vary
1773            between [0, 1].
1774            Each row is in the form of [ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax].
1775     masks: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
1776            [N, height, width] containing instance masks. The masks
1777            are of the same height, width as the input `image`.
1778     keypoints: (optional) rank 3 float32 tensor with shape
1779                [N, num_keypoints, 2]. The keypoints are in y-x normalized
1780                coordinates.
1781     max_height_padding: a scalar tf.int32 tensor denoting the maximum amount of
1782                         height padding. The padding will be chosen uniformly at
1783                         random from [0, max_height_padding).
1784     max_width_padding: a scalar tf.int32 tensor denoting the maximum amount of
1785                        width padding. The padding will be chosen uniformly at
1786                        random from [0, max_width_padding).
1787     pad_color: padding color. A rank 1 tensor of [3] with dtype=tf.float32.
1788                if set as None, it will be set to average color of the input
1789                image.
1790     seed: random seed.
1791     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
1792                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
1793                            function is called multiple times with the same
1794                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
1795 
1796   Returns:
1797     image: Image shape will be [new_height, new_width, channels].
1798     boxes: boxes which is the same rank as input boxes. Boxes are in normalized
1799            form.
1800     if masks is not None, the function also returns:
1801     masks: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape [N, new_height, new_width]
1802     if keypoints is not None, the function also returns:
1803     keypoints: rank 3 float32 tensor with shape [N, num_keypoints, 2]
1804   """
1805   min_image_size = tf.shape(image)[:2]
1806   max_image_size = min_image_size + tf.cast(
1807       [max_height_padding, max_width_padding], dtype=tf.int32)
1808   return random_pad_image(
1809       image,
1810       boxes,
1811       masks=masks,
1812       keypoints=keypoints,
1813       min_image_size=min_image_size,
1814       max_image_size=max_image_size,
1815       pad_color=pad_color,
1816       seed=seed,
1817       preprocess_vars_cache=preprocess_vars_cache)

1820 def random_crop_pad_image(image,
1821                           boxes,
1822                           labels,
1823                           label_weights,
1824                           label_confidences=None,
1825                           multiclass_scores=None,
1826                           min_object_covered=1.0,
1827                           aspect_ratio_range=(0.75, 1.33),
1828                           area_range=(0.1, 1.0),
1829                           overlap_thresh=0.3,
1830                           clip_boxes=True,
1831                           random_coef=0.0,
1832                           min_padded_size_ratio=(1.0, 1.0),
1833                           max_padded_size_ratio=(2.0, 2.0),
1834                           pad_color=None,
1835                           seed=None,
1836                           preprocess_vars_cache=None):
1837   """Randomly crops and pads the image.
1838 
1839   Given an input image and its bounding boxes, this op first randomly crops
1840   the image and then randomly pads the image with background values. Parameters
1841   min_padded_size_ratio and max_padded_size_ratio, determine the range of the
1842   final output image size.  Specifically, the final image size will have a size
1843   in the range of min_padded_size_ratio * tf.shape(image) and
1844   max_padded_size_ratio * tf.shape(image). Note that these ratios are with
1845   respect to the size of the original image, so we can't capture the same
1846   effect easily by independently applying RandomCropImage
1847   followed by RandomPadImage.
1848 
1849   Args:
1850     image: rank 3 float32 tensor containing 1 image -> [height, width, channels]
1851            with pixel values varying between [0, 1].
1852     boxes: rank 2 float32 tensor containing the bounding boxes -> [N, 4].
1853            Boxes are in normalized form meaning their coordinates vary
1854            between [0, 1].
1855            Each row is in the form of [ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax].
1856     labels: rank 1 int32 tensor containing the object classes.
1857     label_weights: rank 1 float32 containing the label weights.
1858     label_confidences: rank 1 float32 containing the label confidences.
1859     multiclass_scores: (optional) float32 tensor of shape
1860       [num_instances, num_classes] representing the score for each box for each
1861       class.
1862     min_object_covered: the cropped image must cover at least this fraction of
1863                         at least one of the input bounding boxes.
1864     aspect_ratio_range: allowed range for aspect ratio of cropped image.
1865     area_range: allowed range for area ratio between cropped image and the
1866                 original image.
1867     overlap_thresh: minimum overlap thresh with new cropped
1868                     image to keep the box.
1869     clip_boxes: whether to clip the boxes to the cropped image.
1870     random_coef: a random coefficient that defines the chance of getting the
1871                  original image. If random_coef is 0, we will always get the
1872                  cropped image, and if it is 1.0, we will always get the
1873                  original image.
1874     min_padded_size_ratio: min ratio of padded image height and width to the
1875                            input image's height and width.
1876     max_padded_size_ratio: max ratio of padded image height and width to the
1877                            input image's height and width.
1878     pad_color: padding color. A rank 1 tensor of [3] with dtype=tf.float32.
1879                if set as None, it will be set to average color of the randomly
1880                cropped image.
1881     seed: random seed.
1882     preprocess_vars_cache: PreprocessorCache object that records previously
1883                            performed augmentations. Updated in-place. If this
1884                            function is called multiple times with the same
1885                            non-null cache, it will perform deterministically.
1886 
1887   Returns:
1888     padded_image: padded image.
1889     padded_boxes: boxes which is the same rank as input boxes. Boxes are in
1890                   normalized form.
1891     cropped_labels: cropped labels.
1892     if label_weights is not None also returns:
1893     cropped_label_weights: cropped label weights.
1894     if multiclass_scores is not None also returns:
1895     cropped_multiclass_scores: cropped_multiclass_scores.
1896 
1897   """
1898   image_size = tf.shape(image)
1899   image_height = image_size[0]
1900   image_width = image_size[1]
1901   result = random_crop_image(
1902       image=image,
1903       boxes=boxes,
1904       labels=labels,
1905       label_weights=label_weights,
1906       label_confidences=label_confidences,
1907       multiclass_scores=multiclass_scores,
1908       min_object_covered=min_object_covered,
1909       aspect_ratio_range=aspect_ratio_range,
1910       area_range=area_range,
1911       overlap_thresh=overlap_thresh,
1912       clip_boxes=clip_boxes,
1913       random_coef=random_coef,
1914       seed=seed,
1915       preprocess_vars_cache=preprocess_vars_cache)
1916 
1917   cropped_image, cropped_boxes, cropped_labels = result[:3]
1918 
1919   min_image_size = tf.cast(
1920       tf.cast(tf.stack([image_height, image_width]), dtype=tf.float32) *
1921       min_padded_size_ratio,
1922       dtype=tf.int32)
1923   max_image_size = tf.cast(
1924       tf.cast(tf.stack([image_height, image_width]), dtype=tf.float32) *
1925       max_padded_size_ratio,
1926       dtype=tf.int32)
1927 
1928   padded_image, padded_boxes = random_pad_image(
1929       cropped_image,
1930       cropped_boxes,
1931       min_image_size=min_image_size,
1932       max_image_size=max_image_size,
1933       pad_color=pad_color,
1934       seed=seed,
1935       preprocess_vars_cache=preprocess_vars_cache)
1936 
1937   cropped_padded_output = (padded_image, padded_boxes, cropped_labels)
1938 
1939   index = 3
1940   if label_weights is not None:
1941     cropped_label_weights = result[index]
1942     cropped_padded_output += (cropped_label_weights,)
1943     index += 1
1944 
1945   if label_confidences is not None:
1946     cropped_label_confidences = result[index]
1947     cropped_padded_output += (cropped_label_confidences,)
1948     index += 1
1949 
1950   if multiclass_scores is not None:
1951     cropped_multiclass_scores = result[index]
1952     cropped_padded_output += (cropped_multiclass_scores,)
1953 
1954   return cropped_padded_output
1955
